      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DEMENTIA (4) was a winner two back when prominent throughout then got further back last time and could manage only a 13 length 7th at this track (18.36). Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Can bounce back. FLYING BLUE MOON (2) had the drop on the lead early on but could only manage second, beaten 1.75 lengths (17.84) at this track in a Grade 5 over 300m. Will give a great sight again. PETA ZOOM (7) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind She's Silky (17.69) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Expecting another good run. BENTLEY ELSA (8) was out of the frame here most recently but can atone.",
